Another set of six COVID-19 patients have been discharged in Borno. The figure of discharged patients in the state on Sunday stands at 12. Six patients were earlier discharged by the UMTH on Sunday. The Committeeâ€™s Chairman and Deputy Governor, Umar Kadafur, confirmed this in a statement in Maiduguri on Sunday evening. He explained out of the 12, six were discharged from the UMTH Isolation centre while the remaining six are from state Isolation centre at Bulabulin Ngaranam. According to him, 22 patients are awaiting the results of their final test and are expected to be discharged in a few days if they negative. 